        "## 🛠️ Developer Reference: CLI Flags\n",
        "If you want to run AutoVSF via command line or custom scripts, use these flags:\n",
        "\n",
        "### 1. `headless.py` (Main Entry Point)\n",
        "| Flag | Description | Default |\n",
        "| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n",
        "| `video` | Path to input video file (Positional) | N/A |\n",
        "| `--top` | Upper boundary for subtitle scan (0.0 - 1.0) | `0.3` |\n",
        "| `--bottom` | Lower boundary for subtitle scan (0.0 - 1.0) | `0.0` |\n",
        "| `--left` | Left boundary for subtitle scan (0.0 - 1.0) | `0.0` |\n",
        "| `--right` | Right boundary for subtitle scan (0.0 - 1.0) | `1.0` |\n",
        "| `--output` | Directory to store temporary RGB images | Auto-generated |\n",
        "| `--skip` | Skip video scanning if images already exist in output dir | `False` |\n",
        "\n",
        "### 2. `ocr.py` (OCR Only)\n",
        "| Flag | Description |\n",
        "| :--- | :--- |\n",
        "| `images_dir` | Directory containing RGB images to OCR (Positional) |\n",
        "| `output_srt` | Path to save the resulting .srt file (Optional) |\n",
        "\n",
        "### 3. VideoSubFinder (Core Engine)\n",
        "Common internal flags used by `headless.py`:\n",
        "- `-c`: Clear output directory.\n",
        "- `-r`: Run feature extraction and search.\n",
        "- `-i <file>`: Input video file.\n",
        "- `-o <dir>`: Output directory.\n",
        "- `-te, -be, -le, -re`: Top, Bottom, Left, Right edges (0.0-1.0)."
      ]
